mtime/ctime based file-over-file conflict management options

  2. Disk Usage Analysis (du command)
  While the stat command provides filesystem-wide statistics, there is no tool for recursive directory-level size calculation. A du command is needed to aggregate and report
  space usage for specific paths across all combined branches.

  9. Extended Attributes (xattr) Support
  Modern filesystems and applications often rely on extended attributes for metadata. Implementing getfattr and setfattr equivalents would bring nofs closer to the
  capabilities of FUSE-based alternatives like mergerfs.

